3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour based on the 8-hour TWAP of the premium between perpetual and mark prices. The on-chain order book ensures transparent price discovery without relying on external oracles for funding calculations. Funding payments occur automatically through smart contracts, with rates typically ranging from -0.1% to +0.1% per 8-hour period, though extreme market conditions can push rates beyond these bounds."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","MKR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MKR perpetuals present compelling arbitrage opportunities due to the token's correlation with DeFi activity cycles and MakerDAO protocol events. The governance token's price sensitivity to protocol upgrades, DAI stability mechanisms, and DeFi market sentiment creates funding rate imbalances. Hyperliquid's hourly funding intervals provide more frequent arbitrage entry points compared to traditional 8-hour cycles."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MKR funding rates on Hyperliquid typically correlate with broader DeFi market cycles and MakerDAO governance events. During DeFi bull runs, long bias often pushes funding rates positive as traders anticipate governance token appreciation. Conversely, during protocol uncertainty or DAI depeg concerns, funding rates can turn sharply negative. The hourly funding mechanism amplifies these patterns, creating 8x more frequent rate adjustments than competing exchanges. Historical data shows MKR funding rates ranging from -2% to +3% during extreme market conditions, with average rates hovering near 0.01% per hour during neutral periods."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategies"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid's unique architecture creates several arbitrage vectors for MKR perpetuals. Cross-exchange funding arbitrage becomes particularly effective when Hyperliquid's hourly rates diverge from Binance or OKX's 8-hour cycles. The on-chain settlement eliminates counterparty risk, allowing for larger position sizes in funding arbitrage strategies. Delta-neutral strategies work well by taking opposing positions on Hyperliquid versus centralized exchanges, capturing funding rate differentials while maintaining market exposure neutrality. The platform's low latency and sub-second finality enable rapid position adjustments when funding rates shift unexpectedly."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Mitigation"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Trading MKR perpetuals on Hyperliquid involves several unique risks beyond standard perpetual trading. The platform's single-chain architecture creates potential liquidity constraints during network congestion, though this rarely affects funding payments. USDC-only collateral limits hedging options compared to multi-collateral exchanges. The newer platform's limited track record requires careful position sizing and monitoring. Cross-exchange arbitrage introduces bridge risks when moving funds between chains. Smart contract risk exists despite audits, making it prudent to avoid concentrating large portions of capital on the platform during its early operational phases."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often are funding rates calculated on Hyperliquid for MKR/USDT?","answer":"Hyperliquid calculates funding rates every hour for all perpetual contracts including MKR/USDT. This is more frequent than most exchanges which use 8-hour intervals, creating additional arbitrage opportunities through more responsive rate adjustments to market conditions."},{"question":"What makes MKR funding rates different on Hyperliquid compared to CEXs?","answer":"Hyperliquid's on-chain order book and hourly funding create more volatile funding rate patterns for MKR. The transparent, oracle-free pricing mechanism often leads to different rate calculations compared to centralized exchanges. Additionally, the DeFi-native user base may have different positioning biases toward governance tokens like MKR."},{"question":"Can I use USDT directly as collateral for MKR perpetuals on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Hyperliquid only accepts USDC as collateral for all perpetual contracts. To trade MKR/USDT perpetuals, you must deposit USDC which serves as margin collateral. The contract settlement and PnL calculations use USDC despite the USDT quote currency in the pair name."},{"question":"What are the typical funding rate ranges for MKR on Hyperliquid?","answer":"MKR funding rates on Hyperliquid typically range from -0.05% to +0.05% per hour during normal market conditions. During high volatility or major DeFi events affecting MakerDAO, rates can spike to ±0.2% per hour. The hourly calculation creates more extreme short-term rates compared to exchanges with 8-hour intervals."}]}]
